DOC_LEVEL: L1
MODULE: runtime
PATH: src/**
DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge

ENTRYPOINT:
- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch

KEY_FILES:
- src/config.js
- src/http/server.js
- src/routes/api-routes.js
- src/services/chat-service.js
- src/adapters/codebuddy.js
- src/bot/telegram.js
- src/services/system-exec-service.js

SUBDIRS:
- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm
- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm
- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm
- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm
- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm
- src/services -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm
- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm

INTERFACES:
- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec
- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, text message relay

TRAPS:
- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true
- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist
- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue

DECISIONS:
- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface
